{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":495,"text":"There is an ancient proverb that says"},{"time":4053,"text":"it's very difficult to find a black cat in a dark room,"},{"time":8115,"text":"especially when there is no cat."},{"time":10903,"text":"I find this a particularly apt description of science"},{"time":14232,"text":"and how science works --"},{"time":16368,"text":"bumbling around in a dark room, bumping into things,"},{"time":19688,"text":"trying to figure out what shape this might be,"},{"time":21990,"text":"what that might be,"},{"time":23434,"text":"there are reports of a cat somewhere around,"},{"time":25923,"text":"they may not be reliable, they may be,"},{"time":27716,"text":"and so forth and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29236,"text":"Now I know this is different than the way most people"},{"time":31212,"text":"think about science."},{"time":32764,"text":"Science, we generally are told,"},{"time":34318,"text":"is a very well-ordered mechanism for"},{"time":37068,"text":"understanding the world,"},{"time":38369,"text":"for gaining facts, for gaining data,"},{"time":40655,"text":"that it's rule-based,"},{"time":42208,"text":"that scientists use this thing called the scientific method"},{"time":45449,"text":"and we've been doing this for 14 generations or so now,"},{"time":48288,"text":"and the scientific method is a set of rules"},{"time":50859,"text":"for getting hard, cold facts out of the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55051,"text":"I'd like to tell you that's not the case."},{"time":57146,"text":"So there's the scientific method,"},{"time":58978,"text":"but what's really going on is this. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":61297,"text":"[The Scientific Method vs. Farting Around]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62255,"text":"And it's going on kind of like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65359,"text":"[... in the dark] (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66780,"text":"So what is the difference, then,"},{"time":71321,"text":"between the way I believe science is pursued"},{"time":75137,"text":"and the way it seems to be perceived?"},{"time":77998,"text":"So this difference first came to me in some ways"},{"time":80713,"text":"in my dual role at Columbia University,"},{"time":82810,"text":"where I'm both a professor and run a laboratory in neuroscience"},{"time":86965,"text":"where we try to figure out how the brain works."},{"time":89160,"text":"We do this by studying the sense of smell,"},{"time":91531,"text":"the sense of olfaction, and in the laboratory,"},{"time":94062,"text":"it's a great pleasure and fascinating work"},{"time":96696,"text":"and exciting to work with graduate students and post-docs"},{"time":99567,"text":"and think up cool experiments to understand how this"},{"time":102178,"text":"sense of smell works and how the brain might be working,"},{"time":104564,"text":"and, well, frankly, it's kind of exhilarating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107366,"text":"But at the same time, it's my responsibility"},{"time":110084,"text":"to teach a large course to undergraduates on the brain,"},{"time":113033,"text":"and that's a big subject,"},{"time":114108,"text":"and it takes quite a while to organize that,"},{"time":116499,"text":"and it's quite challenging and it's quite interesting,"},{"time":119310,"text":"but I have to say, it's not so exhilarating."},{"time":122867,"text":"So what was the difference?"},{"time":124263,"text":"Well, the course I was and am teaching"},{"time":126332,"text":"is called Cellular and Molecular Neuroscience - I. (Laughs)"},{"time":132796,"text":"It's 25 lectures full of all sorts of facts,"},{"time":137351,"text":"it uses this giant book called \"Principles of Neural Science\""},{"time":141668,"text":"by three famous neuroscientists."},{"time":144002,"text":"This book comes in at 1,414 pages,"},{"time":147783,"text":"it weighs a hefty seven and a half pounds."},{"time":150519,"text":"Just to put that in some perspective,"},{"time":152446,"text":"that's the weight of two normal human brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155901,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":159184,"text":"So I began to realize, by the end of this course,"},{"time":162451,"text":"that the students maybe were getting the idea"},{"time":164699,"text":"that we must know everything there is to know about the brain."},{"time":167730,"text":"That's clearly not true."},{"time":169492,"text":"And they must also have this idea, I suppose,"},{"time":172190,"text":"that what scientists do is collect data and collect facts"},{"time":175571,"text":"and stick them in these big books."},{"time":177660,"text":"And that's not really the case either."},{"time":179067,"text":"When I go to a meeting, after the meeting day is over"},{"time":182370,"text":"and we collect in the bar over a couple of beers with my colleagues,"},{"time":185467,"text":"we never talk about what we know."},{"time":187668,"text":"We talk about what we don't know."},{"time":189834,"text":"We talk about what still has to get done,"},{"time":192119,"text":"what's so critical to get done in the lab."},{"time":194944,"text":"Indeed, this was, I think, best said by Marie Curie"},{"time":197501,"text":"who said that one never notices what has been done"},{"time":199920,"text":"but only what remains to be done."},{"time":201381,"text":"This was in a letter to her brother after obtaining"},{"time":203606,"text":"her second graduate degree, I should say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207324,"text":"I have to point out this has always been one of my favorite pictures of Marie Curie,"},{"time":210137,"text":"because I am convinced that that glow behind her"},{"time":212440,"text":"is not a photographic effect. (Laughter)"},{"time":215178,"text":"That's the real thing."},{"time":216978,"text":"It is true that her papers are, to this day,"},{"time":221358,"text":"stored in a basement room in the Bibliothèque Française"},{"time":224237,"text":"in a concrete room that's lead-lined,"},{"time":226434,"text":"and if you're a scholar and you want access to these notebooks,"},{"time":229086,"text":"you have to put on a full radiation hazmat suit,"},{"time":231835,"text":"so it's pretty scary business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234186,"text":"Nonetheless, this is what I think we were leaving out"},{"time":236982,"text":"of our courses"},{"time":238608,"text":"and leaving out of the interaction that we have"},{"time":241134,"text":"with the public as scientists, the what-remains-to-be-done."},{"time":244107,"text":"This is the stuff that's exhilarating and interesting."},{"time":246741,"text":"It is, if you will, the ignorance."},{"time":249651,"text":"That's what was missing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250630,"text":"So I thought, well, maybe I should teach a course"},{"time":253490,"text":"on ignorance,"},{"time":255590,"text":"something I can finally excel at, perhaps, for example."},{"time":259219,"text":"So I did start teaching this course on ignorance,"},{"time":261097,"text":"and it's been quite interesting"},{"time":262193,"text":"and I'd like to tell you to go to the website."},{"time":264279,"text":"You can find all sorts of information there. It's wide open."},{"time":267915,"text":"And it's been really quite an interesting time for me"},{"time":271438,"text":"to meet up with other scientists who come in and talk"},{"time":273279,"text":"about what it is they don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274827,"text":"Now I use this word \"ignorance,\" of course,"},{"time":276812,"text":"to be at least in part intentionally provocative,"},{"time":279970,"text":"because ignorance has a lot of bad connotations"},{"time":282360,"text":"and I clearly don't mean any of those."},{"time":284365,"text":"So I don't mean stupidity, I don't mean a callow indifference"},{"time":287870,"text":"to fact or reason or data."},{"time":290178,"text":"The ignorant are clearly unenlightened, unaware,"},{"time":293449,"text":"uninformed, and present company today excepted,"},{"time":296756,"text":"often occupy elected offices, it seems to me."},{"time":299664,"text":"That's another story, perhaps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301470,"text":"I mean a different kind of ignorance."},{"time":303103,"text":"I mean a kind of ignorance that's less pejorative,"},{"time":305371,"text":"a kind of ignorance that comes from a communal gap in our knowledge,"},{"time":308858,"text":"something that's just not there to be known"},{"time":310723,"text":"or isn't known well enough yet or we can't make predictions from,"},{"time":313544,"text":"the kind of ignorance that's maybe best summed up"},{"time":315862,"text":"in a statement by James Clerk Maxwell,"},{"time":317707,"text":"perhaps the greatest physicist between Newton and Einstein,"},{"time":321156,"text":"who said, \"Thoroughly conscious ignorance"},{"time":323457,"text":"is the prelude to every real advance in science.\""},{"time":326025,"text":"I think it's a wonderful idea:"},{"time":327413,"text":"thoroughly conscious ignorance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330560,"text":"So that's the kind of ignorance that I want to talk about today,"},{"time":332981,"text":"but of course the first thing we have to clear up"},{"time":334500,"text":"is what are we going to do with all those facts?"},{"time":336603,"text":"So it is true that science piles up at an alarming rate."},{"time":340277,"text":"We all have this sense that science is this mountain of facts,"},{"time":343087,"text":"this accumulation model of science, as many have called it,"},{"time":347123,"text":"and it seems impregnable, it seems impossible."},{"time":349574,"text":"How can you ever know all of this?"},{"time":350888,"text":"And indeed, the scientific literature grows at an alarming rate."},{"time":354469,"text":"In 2006, there were 1.3 million papers published."},{"time":358123,"text":"There's about a two-and-a-half-percent yearly growth rate,"},{"time":360755,"text":"and so last year we saw over one and a half million papers being published."},{"time":365145,"text":"Divide that by the number of minutes in a year,"},{"time":367375,"text":"and you wind up with three new papers per minute."},{"time":370513,"text":"So I've been up here a little over 10 minutes,"},{"time":371995,"text":"I've already lost three papers."},{"time":373771,"text":"I have to get out of here actually. I have to go read."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376611,"text":"So what do we do about this? Well, the fact is"},{"time":380057,"text":"that what scientists do about it is a kind of a controlled neglect, if you will."},{"time":384566,"text":"We just don't worry about it, in a way."},{"time":387230,"text":"The facts are important. You have to know a lot of stuff"},{"time":389473,"text":"to be a scientist. That's true."},{"time":391283,"text":"But knowing a lot of stuff doesn't make you a scientist."},{"time":394210,"text":"You need to know a lot of stuff to be a lawyer"},{"time":396875,"text":"or an accountant or an electrician or a carpenter."},{"time":400767,"text":"But in science, knowing a lot of stuff is not the point."},{"time":404377,"text":"Knowing a lot of stuff is there to help you get"},{"time":407933,"text":"to more ignorance."},{"time":409321,"text":"So knowledge is a big subject, but I would say"},{"time":411831,"text":"ignorance is a bigger one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414318,"text":"So this leads us to maybe think about, a little bit"},{"time":416528,"text":"about, some of the models of science that we tend to use,"},{"time":419411,"text":"and I'd like to disabuse you of some of them."},{"time":421236,"text":"So one of them, a popular one, is that scientists"},{"time":423549,"text":"are patiently putting the pieces of a puzzle together"},{"time":426177,"text":"to reveal some grand scheme or another."},{"time":428950,"text":"This is clearly not true. For one, with puzzles,"},{"time":431508,"text":"the manufacturer has guaranteed that there's a solution."},{"time":435007,"text":"We don't have any such guarantee."},{"time":436756,"text":"Indeed, there are many of us who aren't so sure about the manufacturer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439911,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442974,"text":"So I think the puzzle model doesn't work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444731,"text":"Another popular model is that science is busy unraveling things"},{"time":448245,"text":"the way you unravel the peels of an onion."},{"time":450441,"text":"So peel by peel, you take away the layers of the onion"},{"time":453430,"text":"to get at some fundamental kernel of truth."},{"time":455749,"text":"I don't think that's the way it works either."},{"time":457936,"text":"Another one, a kind of popular one, is the iceberg idea,"},{"time":460870,"text":"that we only see the tip of the iceberg but underneath"},{"time":463330,"text":"is where most of the iceberg is hidden."},{"time":465515,"text":"But all of these models are based on the idea of a large body of facts"},{"time":469069,"text":"that we can somehow or another get completed."},{"time":471489,"text":"We can chip away at this iceberg and figure out what it is,"},{"time":474832,"text":"or we could just wait for it to melt, I suppose, these days,"},{"time":477437,"text":"but one way or another we could get to the whole iceberg. Right?"},{"time":480664,"text":"Or make it manageable. But I don't think that's the case."},{"time":483131,"text":"I think what really happens in science"},{"time":485530,"text":"is a model more like the magic well,"},{"time":487360,"text":"where no matter how many buckets you take out,"},{"time":489197,"text":"there's always another bucket of water to be had,"},{"time":491309,"text":"or my particularly favorite one,"},{"time":493436,"text":"with the effect and everything, the ripples on a pond."},{"time":496375,"text":"So if you think of knowledge being this ever-expanding ripple on a pond,"},{"time":499502,"text":"the important thing to realize is that our ignorance,"},{"time":502884,"text":"the circumference of this knowledge, also grows with knowledge."},{"time":506266,"text":"So the knowledge generates ignorance."},{"time":509029,"text":"This is really well said, I thought, by George Bernard Shaw."},{"time":511944,"text":"This is actually part of a toast that he delivered"},{"time":514621,"text":"to celebrate Einstein at a dinner celebrating Einstein's work,"},{"time":518298,"text":"in which he claims that science"},{"time":519712,"text":"just creates more questions than it answers.\n[\"Science is always wrong. It never solves a problem without creating 10 more.\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521977,"text":"I find that kind of glorious, and I think he's precisely right,"},{"time":525519,"text":"plus it's a kind of job security."},{"time":528045,"text":"As it turns out, he kind of cribbed that"},{"time":530771,"text":"from the philosopher Immanuel Kant"},{"time":532623,"text":"who a hundred years earlier had come up with this idea"},{"time":535268,"text":"of question propagation, that every answer begets more questions."},{"time":539076,"text":"I love that term, \"question propagation,\""},{"time":541275,"text":"this idea of questions propagating out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544014,"text":"So I'd say the model we want to take is not"},{"time":545901,"text":"that we start out kind of ignorant and we get some facts together"},{"time":549410,"text":"and then we gain knowledge."},{"time":551553,"text":"It's rather kind of the other way around, really."},{"time":553932,"text":"What do we use this knowledge for?"},{"time":555839,"text":"What are we using this collection of facts for?"},{"time":558367,"text":"We're using it to make better ignorance,"},{"time":561224,"text":"to come up with, if you will, higher-quality ignorance."},{"time":564303,"text":"Because, you know, there's low-quality ignorance"},{"time":566175,"text":"and there's high-quality ignorance. It's not all the same."},{"time":568588,"text":"Scientists argue about this all the time."},{"time":570958,"text":"Sometimes we call them bull sessions."},{"time":572923,"text":"Sometimes we call them grant proposals."},{"time":574841,"text":"But nonetheless, it's what the argument is about."},{"time":578349,"text":"It's the ignorance. It's the what we don't know."},{"time":580193,"text":"It's what makes a good question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582883,"text":"So how do we think about these questions?"},{"time":584513,"text":"I'm going to show you a graph that shows up"},{"time":586465,"text":"quite a bit on happy hour posters in various science departments."},{"time":590332,"text":"This graph asks the relationship between what you know"},{"time":594553,"text":"and how much you know about it."},{"time":596743,"text":"So what you know, you can know anywhere from nothing to everything, of course,"},{"time":600258,"text":"and how much you know about it can be anywhere"},{"time":601941,"text":"from a little to a lot."},{"time":604364,"text":"So let's put a point on the graph. There's an undergraduate."},{"time":608596,"text":"Doesn't know much but they have a lot of interest."},{"time":610960,"text":"They're interested in almost everything."},{"time":612651,"text":"Now you look at a master's student, a little further along in their education,"},{"time":616105,"text":"and you see they know a bit more,"},{"time":617456,"text":"but it's been narrowed somewhat."},{"time":619346,"text":"And finally you get your Ph.D., where it turns out"},{"time":622065,"text":"you know a tremendous amount about almost nothing. (Laughter)"},{"time":627170,"text":"What's really disturbing is the trend line that goes through that"},{"time":630951,"text":"because, of course, when it dips below the zero axis, there,"},{"time":634726,"text":"it gets into a negative area."},{"time":636988,"text":"That's where you find people like me, I'm afraid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639903,"text":"So the important thing here is that this can all be changed."},{"time":643271,"text":"This whole view can be changed"},{"time":645075,"text":"by just changing the label on the x-axis."},{"time":648236,"text":"So instead of how much you know about it,"},{"time":650153,"text":"we could say, \"What can you ask about it?\""},{"time":653694,"text":"So yes, you do need to know a lot of stuff as a scientist,"},{"time":656561,"text":"but the purpose of knowing a lot of stuff"},{"time":659190,"text":"is not just to know a lot of stuff. That just makes you a geek, right?"},{"time":661777,"text":"Knowing a lot of stuff, the purpose is"},{"time":663915,"text":"to be able to ask lots of questions,"},{"time":665591,"text":"to be able to frame thoughtful, interesting questions,"},{"time":668679,"text":"because that's where the real work is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670404,"text":"Let me give you a quick idea of a couple of these sorts of questions."},{"time":672956,"text":"I'm a neuroscientist, so how would we come up"},{"time":675119,"text":"with a question in neuroscience?"},{"time":676550,"text":"Because it's not always quite so straightforward."},{"time":679219,"text":"So, for example, we could say, well what is it that the brain does?"},{"time":681778,"text":"Well, one thing the brain does, it moves us around."},{"time":683592,"text":"We walk around on two legs."},{"time":685597,"text":"That seems kind of simple, somehow or another."},{"time":687448,"text":"I mean, virtually everybody over 10 months of age"},{"time":690173,"text":"walks around on two legs, right?"},{"time":692345,"text":"So that maybe is not that interesting."},{"time":693736,"text":"So instead maybe we want to choose something a little more complicated to look at."},{"time":696884,"text":"How about the visual system?"},{"time":699659,"text":"There it is, the visual system."},{"time":701286,"text":"I mean, we love our visual systems. We do all kinds of cool stuff."},{"time":704534,"text":"Indeed, there are over 12,000 neuroscientists"},{"time":707925,"text":"who work on the visual system,"},{"time":709505,"text":"from the retina to the visual cortex,"},{"time":711586,"text":"in an attempt to understand not just the visual system"},{"time":714151,"text":"but to also understand how general principles"},{"time":717175,"text":"of how the brain might work."},{"time":719126,"text":"But now here's the thing:"},{"time":720786,"text":"Our technology has actually been pretty good"},{"time":723266,"text":"at replicating what the visual system does."},{"time":725856,"text":"We have TV, we have movies,"},{"time":728879,"text":"we have animation, we have photography,"},{"time":731374,"text":"we have pattern recognition, all of these sorts of things."},{"time":734525,"text":"They work differently than our visual systems in some cases,"},{"time":737171,"text":"but nonetheless we've been pretty good at"},{"time":738762,"text":"making a technology work like our visual system."},{"time":742238,"text":"Somehow or another, a hundred years of robotics,"},{"time":745174,"text":"you never saw a robot walk on two legs,"},{"time":747440,"text":"because robots don't walk on two legs"},{"time":749603,"text":"because it's not such an easy thing to do."},{"time":751993,"text":"A hundred years of robotics,"},{"time":753521,"text":"and we can't get a robot that can move more than a couple steps one way or the other."},{"time":756888,"text":"You ask them to go up an inclined plane, and they fall over."},{"time":759460,"text":"Turn around, and they fall over. It's a serious problem."},{"time":761464,"text":"So what is it that's the most difficult thing for a brain to do?"},{"time":765011,"text":"What ought we to be studying?"},{"time":766634,"text":"Perhaps it ought to be walking on two legs, or the motor system."},{"time":770929,"text":"I'll give you an example from my own lab,"},{"time":772664,"text":"my own particularly smelly question,"},{"time":774389,"text":"since we work on the sense of smell."},{"time":776488,"text":"But here's a diagram of five molecules"},{"time":779716,"text":"and sort of a chemical notation."},{"time":781226,"text":"These are just plain old molecules, but if you sniff those molecules"},{"time":784222,"text":"up these two little holes in the front of your face,"},{"time":786692,"text":"you will have in your mind the distinct impression of a rose."},{"time":790566,"text":"If there's a real rose there, those molecules will be the ones,"},{"time":792724,"text":"but even if there's no rose there,"},{"time":794284,"text":"you'll have the memory of a molecule."},{"time":795875,"text":"How do we turn molecules into perceptions?"},{"time":798979,"text":"What's the process by which that could happen?"},{"time":800836,"text":"Here's another example: two very simple molecules, again in this kind of chemical notation."},{"time":804796,"text":"It might be easier to visualize them this way,"},{"time":806873,"text":"so the gray circles are carbon atoms, the white ones"},{"time":809667,"text":"are hydrogen atoms and the red ones are oxygen atoms."},{"time":812442,"text":"Now these two molecules differ by only one carbon atom"},{"time":816740,"text":"and two little hydrogen atoms that ride along with it,"},{"time":819428,"text":"and yet one of them, heptyl acetate,"},{"time":821414,"text":"has the distinct odor of a pear,"},{"time":823725,"text":"and hexyl acetate is unmistakably banana."},{"time":827564,"text":"So there are two really interesting questions here, it seems to me."},{"time":830121,"text":"One is, how can a simple little molecule like that"},{"time":833336,"text":"create a perception in your brain that's so clear"},{"time":835804,"text":"as a pear or a banana?"},{"time":837546,"text":"And secondly, how the hell can we tell the difference"},{"time":840667,"text":"between two molecules that differ by a single carbon atom?"},{"time":844982,"text":"I mean, that's remarkable to me,"},{"time":846628,"text":"clearly the best chemical detector on the face of the planet."},{"time":849660,"text":"And you don't even think about it, do you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":852436,"text":"So this is a favorite quote of mine that takes us"},{"time":855053,"text":"back to the ignorance and the idea of questions."},{"time":856799,"text":"I like to quote because I think dead people"},{"time":858818,"text":"shouldn't be excluded from the conversation."},{"time":861361,"text":"And I also think it's important to realize that"},{"time":863300,"text":"the conversation's been going on for a while, by the way."},{"time":865762,"text":"So Erwin Schrodinger, a great quantum physicist"},{"time":868520,"text":"and, I think, philosopher, points out how you have to"},{"time":871086,"text":"\"abide by ignorance for an indefinite period\" of time."},{"time":874551,"text":"And it's this abiding by ignorance"},{"time":876538,"text":"that I think we have to learn how to do."},{"time":878204,"text":"This is a tricky thing. This is not such an easy business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881181,"text":"I guess it comes down to our education system,"},{"time":883140,"text":"so I'm going to talk a little bit about ignorance and education,"},{"time":885597,"text":"because I think that's where it really has to play out."},{"time":887865,"text":"So for one, let's face it,"},{"time":890132,"text":"in the age of Google and Wikipedia,"},{"time":893484,"text":"the business model of the university"},{"time":895277,"text":"and probably secondary schools is simply going to have to change."},{"time":898698,"text":"We just can't sell facts for a living anymore."},{"time":900599,"text":"They're available with a click of the mouse,"},{"time":902649,"text":"or if you want to, you could probably just ask the wall"},{"time":905145,"text":"one of these days, wherever they're going to hide the things"},{"time":906857,"text":"that tell us all this stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":908274,"text":"So what do we have to do? We have to give our students"},{"time":911157,"text":"a taste for the boundaries, for what's outside that circumference,"},{"time":915053,"text":"for what's outside the facts, what's just beyond the facts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919361,"text":"How do we do that?"},{"time":921518,"text":"Well, one of the problems, of course,"},{"time":923026,"text":"turns out to be testing."},{"time":925135,"text":"We currently have an educational system"},{"time":927784,"text":"which is very efficient but is very efficient at a rather bad thing."},{"time":931493,"text":"So in second grade, all the kids are interested in science,"},{"time":934467,"text":"the girls and the boys."},{"time":935730,"text":"They like to take stuff apart. They have great curiosity."},{"time":939704,"text":"They like to investigate things. They go to science museums."},{"time":942203,"text":"They like to play around. They're in second grade."},{"time":948407,"text":"They're interested."},{"time":949901,"text":"But by 11th or 12th grade, fewer than 10 percent"},{"time":952835,"text":"of them have any interest in science whatsoever,"},{"time":955910,"text":"let alone a desire to go into science as a career."},{"time":958855,"text":"So we have this remarkably efficient system"},{"time":961837,"text":"for beating any interest in science out of everybody's head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":965810,"text":"Is this what we want?"},{"time":967724,"text":"I think this comes from what a teacher colleague of mine"},{"time":970066,"text":"calls \"the bulimic method of education.\""},{"time":972788,"text":"You know. You can imagine what it is."},{"time":974161,"text":"We just jam a whole bunch of facts down their throats over here"},{"time":977109,"text":"and then they puke it up on an exam over here"},{"time":979463,"text":"and everybody goes home with no added intellectual heft whatsoever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984042,"text":"This can't possibly continue to go on."},{"time":986123,"text":"So what do we do? Well the geneticists, I have to say,"},{"time":988457,"text":"have an interesting maxim they live by."},{"time":990440,"text":"Geneticists always say, you always get what you screen for."},{"time":995692,"text":"And that's meant as a warning."},{"time":998553,"text":"So we always will get what we screen for,"},{"time":1000872,"text":"and part of what we screen for is in our testing methods."},{"time":1004327,"text":"Well, we hear a lot about testing and evaluation,"},{"time":1007570,"text":"and we have to think carefully when we're testing"},{"time":1009757,"text":"whether we're evaluating or whether we're weeding,"},{"time":1012844,"text":"whether we're weeding people out,"},{"time":1014303,"text":"whether we're making some cut."},{"time":1017437,"text":"Evaluation is one thing. You hear a lot about evaluation"},{"time":1020078,"text":"in the literature these days, in the educational literature,"},{"time":1022988,"text":"but evaluation really amounts to feedback and it amounts"},{"time":1025946,"text":"to an opportunity for trial and error."},{"time":1028100,"text":"It amounts to a chance to work over a longer period of time"},{"time":1032594,"text":"with this kind of feedback."},{"time":1034504,"text":"That's different than weeding, and usually, I have to tell you,"},{"time":1037442,"text":"when people talk about evaluation, evaluating students,"},{"time":1040168,"text":"evaluating teachers, evaluating schools,"},{"time":1042955,"text":"evaluating programs, that they're really talking about weeding."},{"time":1047116,"text":"And that's a bad thing, because then you will get what you select for,"},{"time":1051326,"text":"which is what we've gotten so far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053284,"text":"So I'd say what we need is a test that says, \"What is x?\""},{"time":1056725,"text":"and the answers are \"I don't know, because no one does,\""},{"time":1059817,"text":"or \"What's the question?\" Even better."},{"time":1061558,"text":"Or, \"You know what, I'll look it up, I'll ask someone,"},{"time":1063964,"text":"I'll phone someone. I'll find out.\""},{"time":1066664,"text":"Because that's what we want people to do,"},{"time":1068214,"text":"and that's how you evaluate them."},{"time":1069585,"text":"And maybe for the advanced placement classes,"},{"time":1071528,"text":"it could be, \"Here's the answer. What's the next question?\""},{"time":1075242,"text":"That's the one I like in particular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076753,"text":"So let me end with a quote from William Butler Yeats,"},{"time":1078930,"text":"who said \"Education is not about filling buckets;"},{"time":1082097,"text":"it is lighting fires.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1084250,"text":"So I'd say, let's get out the matches."},{"time":1088125,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1089333,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1092560,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}